        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 4:56AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 456 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Wilburton, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Kanima...                         Damon...
Briartown...                      Whitefield...
Panola...                         Robbers Cave State Park...
Kinta...                          Wilburton...
Keota...                          Stigler...
Lequire...                        Lewisville...
Mccurtain...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM CDT for
southeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
